---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Home
---

{% set latestThought = collections.thoughts | last %}

<section class="reaction-zone" style="width: 100%; margin-top: 2rem;">
    <div id="cusdis_thread"
      data-host="https://cusdis.com"
      data-app-id="4389d248-f290-48a7-9aed-55511f2e8471"
      data-page-id="{{ latestThought.fileSlug }}"
      data-page-url="https://blindmouse.au/archive/{{ latestThought.fileSlug }}"
      data-page-title="{{ latestThought.date | readableDate }}"
      data-theme="dark"
    ></div>
    <script async defer src="https://cusdis.com/js/cusdis.es.js"></script>
</section>

<section class="reaction-zone">
    <div class="input-container">
        <div class="input-icon">💭</div>
        <input type="text" class="reaction-input" placeholder="React to this thought...">
        <button class="send-btn">Send</button>
    </div>

    <div class="recent-reactions">
        <div class="bubble">
            <p>That web dashboard sounds like a great idea. It would make monitoring so much easier on a second monitor.</p>
            <span class="bubble-time">10 mins ago</span>
        </div>
        <div class="bubble">
            <p>Are you using Flask or FastAPI for the backend?</p>
            <span class="bubble-time">1 hour ago</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="archive-action">
    <a href="/archive" class="btn-archive">View Archive of Daily Thoughts</a>
</section>
